  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Expert Advisory Call Down Service - DCP Ghana 686: Regulatory Guillotine Expert to lead high-level engagement and planning with Government for RG Implementation in Ghana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The UK will provide up to &#xA3;10 million over 2015-2019 through the BEEP to help the Business Enabling Environment in Ghana. Funding will support targeted institutions within the Government of Ghana to enact reforms; build the evidence base for reform through independent analysis and research; and support Public-Private innovative and effective approaches.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of the assignment is to secure high level political buy-in from the President/Vice-President on the adoption of the Regulatory Guillotine approach and associated components. This is expected to ensure that Ghana is by businesses and international reviewers as a country with good quality business regulations, where cost-savings and transparency/predictability is given high priority.</narrative>
  </description>
